<FONT SIZE="1" color="#000000" face="Verdana, Arial">
posted November 25, 2000 05:38 AM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=3&t=002068&reply_num=000000&u="><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=3&t=002068&replyto=000000"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Mages have a unique grouping problem especially at high lvls that not many people seem to have mentioned.<P>Let’s not look at what Mages can or cannot contribute to a group first.  But let’s look at what classes work best with Mages and what classes clash with Mages in groups.<P>Druids and Rangers (and Necros at times) hate Mages using Earth pet due to the pet’s root cancelling snare.  Enchanters hate pets big time since they mess up their Mes.  But due to the demographics of players at high lvls, Mages are usually forced to play "other people’s game", ie, giving up the natural way Mages would have played but to adapt to the Enchanter/Druid/Warrior/Cleric playstyle.<P>Most classes are created to be class inter-dependent (Warriors and Clerics are a pair etc).  Having 4 Warriors or 4 Clerics or 4 Enchanters in a group will not give you an effective combination.  But Mages are created to work best when there are more of the same.  Mages group best with other Mages.  When the main power in a group is Mage, ie, a group with 3 to 4 Mages, they will be allowed to play in their natural way and they can be even stronger than an Enchanter/Druid/Warrior/Cleric group.<P>Are Necros in the same boat? No.  Due to how DOT works, 4 Necros is not 4 times the power as in the case for Mages.  Also, Mages can chain-cast pets in a Mage dominating group to create an unending supply of tanking while Necros cannot.<P>But since too many Mages have to force themselves to adapt to the Enchanter/Druid/Warrior/Cleric playstyle at high lvls, alot of them think the Mage class is either under-powered or no more fun.  More and more lvl 50+ Mages are retired and it only becomes harder to create groups with 4 Mages to allow Mages to play in their natural way again and to feel the real power of Mages.  And thus, the downward spiral begins and Mages are doomed to play "other people’s game".<P>Mages, Necros and Druids are the 3 soloing classes that have to adapt to a "must group" environment at high lvls.  But only Mages is a stacking class (more Mages the better) while Necros and Druids can adapt to a class inter-dependent situation.<BR>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
