<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Maybe I should elaborate a bit more on what I mean by the natural mentality of mages if they are allowed to grow up without being indoctrinated by the tank/cleric playstyle.<P>If there are two mages in a group and there are two mobs, the mage's natural mentality is to stick one earth pet on each mob and then nuke the weaker one first.  But in a tank heavy group, mages are always expected to stick all pets on the same mob and usually the stronger one first.<P>In a dungeon group with 3 to 4 mages, checking to make sure that there is one pet on every mob is the main job (resummon if pet is near death as well).  The assist hotkey is not for the pet to assist the tank (or other pets) but for the mage to assist the nuker.<P>There are fundamental differences like these that mages grew up to accept without questioning anymore.  And so, by lvl 50+, mages find their class no fun anymore and even if they get the chance to group with a mage heavy group, they lack the training to play as a mage can play.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
