<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
My point is, I do not think Mages are not group friendly at all ).  But Mages are only group friendly with other Mages.<P>If you find that the Mage class is no longer fun or if you feel that you are having a hard time adapting to an un-natural group playstyle, go team up with 3 other Mages.  Then look for two other memebers of any class to fill up the group.  In a group like this, you will finally feel comfortable and those other two members of random classes will realise how group friendly Mages can be.<P>If Mages start doing this at low to mid lvls, they gain the practice to play like a mage in a group, they will find the class more fun at higher lvls and they can educate other classes of the Mage way to group.<P>Most lvl 50+ of other classes who graduated their lvl 40s killing Seafuries in OOT have a lot more respect and understanding of Mage's grouping powers.  <P>We cannot expect other classes to understand us unless we show them.  And we have to start doing that at low lvls.
