as a wizard, im gonna go ahead and say, unless there is an enchanter, anyone who tells you not to use your pet for crowd control and damage absorbtion better have a damn good reason for it.  dont conform!<BR>mages are great in groups, their pets are even more valuable.  the super healing they have means they can tank the second mob every fight.  its like the one group i was in with a warrior, a druid, a shaman, and me, a wizard.  i kept snaring the mob nuking it, and running it in circles for all to attack.  wala! no downtime, no damage incurred.  because the warrior says, "i refuse to chase ofter a mob," i complied, and eventually left the group.  each tiger we pulled, the warrior took huge damage, and couldn't even keep teh mob on him if i nuked it at 30% health remaining.  why did he want it that way? he couldn't stand to play the assist class even once.  <P>druids hate people over-riding their snares.  most enches are unwilling to try a group w/o using mez.  ive had chanters tell the warrior to pull a bunch of multiples just so teh chanter can say look at me, i mezzed them alll, woopedooo.  tanks are afraid to join in the kiting, when in reality they can kite it up as well as any other class.  to some extent, mages dont want to unsummon good old muddy in exchange for another one.  <P>now, most of the time these standardized tactics work, but when you get a chance to break the mold and try relying on something other than tank/cleric and everyone playing back up, well, GO FOR IT!
