<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Here is replay of necro lvl 54...<BR>Oki firsty necro DO stack and more necro is better as well ... in some cases:<BR>6 necro can and DID brake and CLEAN  plan of fear - 6 mages cannt (sorry folks - you cannt FD pull, you cannt heal each other, you dont have what so ever crowed control).<BR>Necro dots alike common believing DO stacks - problem is they stack across lines not in same line (except poison and desease those stack inside line as well) and single necro simply cannt keep memed em all. As for grouping - the only pet that actualy cause problem in dangeons - earthy - root screw big time snare and darness - result - trains<BR>Second problem with mages thye dont have anything unique to offer group that is ESSENTIAL - well except one thing CoH.<BR>Let put this way - necropets damage vise past 50s about as good as mages one but have much lower hp - never the less again alike common believe necro CAN chain cast pets even 59 sommon (650 mana not a big deal taking in account 32 mana per tic mana regeneration that necro have). DD? well - druid, wizzards can nuke for more and shamans can nuke manaless via armor. Resist debuff? - well shamans one superior over mage one add here shaman also can debuff atk speed which is more important. DS? - well after mob slowed or even better chain stunned well not much damage - most groups simply dont bother with it even then have mage or druid in group. <BR>Look what can offer to group druid lvl 60 - complete heal, nuke on 1024, regeneration, HP buff, evac, snare<BR>Look what necro lvl 60 can offer group - mean pet, damage ~5000 per 96 second, manatransfer (taking in account that most necro specialize in alteration ratio of trasfer close to 2:1 which isnt bad), minor heal for caster, limited crowed control<BR>Look on mage now - superior pet and CoH, mediorose resist bebuff, medioroce DD, modulation rod<BR>Well I really glad that result of mage epic is spell that give you super pet - conjuration its where mages shine - except I really hate see this pet in group for one single reason - its dispelling  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/frown.gif"> so no dots no snare no mes no root ect ...<BR>Where is no special style at high lvls that you refer - just face fact no matter how mean eath pet it cannt replace real tank at 50s, no matter how fast you can chain cast pets then you got caught by train or bad pull - nothing you can do w/o enchanter. <BR>At the end I'd say that 2 mages in group no better then 2 wizzard or druid and certanly worst then 2 necro but any classes more one per group except melee is overkill
